CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 31, 1956, pg. A26 reads: "Cherry Blossom Queen - Miss Alvernize Barr, center, was the "Cherry Blossom Queen" at the annual Palm Sunday Symposium given by the National Achievement Clubs, Inc. Pictured with Miss Barr, left, Mrs. Mamie Williams, and right, mrs. Gloria Bassett. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait four women, left to right: Jessie Vann, Mamie Williams, "Cherry Blossom Queen" Alvernize Barr, and Gloria Bassett, for National Achievement Clubs, Inc. Symposium
